FOCUS MODIFIER --USE ON FORMS AND INPUT FIELDS


.bg-blue-500


.focus:bg-blue-500


Hover Classes


.focus:bg-*              ====== background color

.focus:text-{color}-{shade} === text color

.focus:font-bold ============== font weight

.focus:border-{color}-{shade} == border color

Working with a simple input field:

<body class="h-screen bg-gray-200 flex justify-center items-center p-6">

        
<input class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-lg py-2 px-4 block w-full" type="email" placeholder="jane@example.com">
</body>


Adding a blue color when focus:

focus:bg-blue-200

<body class="h-screen bg-gray-200 flex justify-center items-center p-6">
        
<input class="bg-white focus:bg-blue-200 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg py-2 px-4 block w-full" type="email" placeholder="jane@example.com">
        
</body>









